<div class="page-header">Nix Primer</div>
<section id="Overview">
  <div class="p">
    Nix is a relatively lightweight, portable, and elegant package
    management system. 'Nix' may also refer to the functional language
    used to describe packages. Here, we provide an overview of both
    sufficient to get one started using nix to develop 'micro
    distributions' for use in development and production environments.
  </div>
  <div class="p">
    The primer is organized into a series of topics. The series is
    ordered for the benefit of those new to nix. Each topic is
    designed as an elementary reference as well.
  </div>
</section>
<section id="Topics">
  <h1>Topics</h1>
  <div class="p">
    <ul>
      <li>
	<em><a href="/documentation/nix-primer/Nix-in-Context">Nix in Context</a></em>:
	A high level look at how nix fits in the stack.
      </li>
      <li>
	<em><a href="/documentation/nix-primer/Use-Cases">Use Cases</a></em>:
	How and why use nix?
      </li>
      <li>
	<em><a href="/documentation/nix-primer/Building-Packages">Building
	Packages</a></em>: Walk through using nix-expressions to build
	packages.
      </li>
      <li>
	<em><a href="/documentation/nix-primer/Basic-Admin">Basic
	Admin</a></em>: Run through basic nix administration.
      </li>
      <li>
	<em><a href="/documentation/nix-primer/Development-Integeration">Development
	Integration</a></em>: Patterns to integrate nix with
	development.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
